Job Description:
Challenge

Hiber (hiber.global) is a young and fast growing company in the Internet of Things sector. Did you know that 90% of the globe has no affordable connectivity? So how can we ensure the fishing industry to be sustainable, improve the water usage whilst improving crop yields, and reduce the carbon footprints within the transportation sector? The answer is Hiber: by using a constellation of satellites we enable IoT for remote and rural areas. With our solutions, the opportunities for all types of businesses are boundless.
Hiber makes it possible to bring this hightech solution from space back to earth with simplicity and ease of use. As a Global Business Development expert you are going show the world that remote IoT at scale is closer than ever before. Therefore, as a Sales Pioneer, you are expected to use your commercial experience to bring our solutions for the heavy equipment & logistics industry to market and explore new businesses and opportunities in those industries. As a result of the nature of the product, the sales process is very much a consultative selling process.
Responsibilities
Develop and manage sales pipeline;
Find and engage with decision makers;
Plan, prepare and execute sales meetings and visit relevant international conferences;
Identify and communicate strong use cases within the targeted organisations;
Manage negotiation of contracts;
Accurately forecast revenue growth and achieve it.
The three necessary building blocks for this profession: an in-depth knowledge of the customers, effective knowledge of the product being sold, and extensive domain expertise.
What’s in it for you?
Working with truly experienced professionals,
Inspirational innovative start-up environment,
Being a part of a groundbreaking innovation with 21st century tech pioneers,
Flexible hours, work-from-home options, office lunch, sauna, gym, chill floor (pool table, bar, dj set) and so much more!
Requirements

You love tech and have...
A relevant Bachelor/Master's’ degree;
A clear understanding of how (IoT) data can improve the financial sector, from banking or insurance companies to different financial products. You also understand how those companies' end customers in primary industries like mining, agriculture, and logistics benefit from IoT
At least 5-7 years of experience with consultative selling of financial products/ services and/or data solutions to the mining, agriculture and/ or logistics market.
Strong experience with selling directly to end-customers, partner sales experience is a plus
Proven success penetrating new markets and closing new business;
Great people skills. You enjoy engaging with prospects, talking about their business and how the company can provide solutions for their business needs;
Exceptional written and verbal communication skills are fluent,
Fluency in English, Dutch and a third language is preferred.

Interessante en veelzijdige stageplaats voor 5 of 6 maanden vanaf september;
Veel verantwoordelijkheid en ruimte voor eigen initiatieven;
